  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>-1</option><replaceable> file1</replaceable></term>
  <listitem>
<para>Specify the name of the file containing the initial image for interpolate. If op
<option>-2</option>
exist we interpolate between a black image and the existing file ('fondu au noir
<emphasis remap='I'>file1</emphasis>
is '-' standard input is used.</para>
  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>-2</option><replaceable> file2</replaceable></term>
  <listitem>
<para>Specify the name of the file containing the initial image for interpolate. If op
<option>-1</option>
exist we interpolate between a black image and the existing file ('fondu au noir
<emphasis remap='I'>file2</emphasis>
is '-' standard input is used.</para>
  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry>
  <term><option>-n</option><replaceable> nbimages</replaceable></term>
  <listitem>
<para>Specify The number of images to create. By default nbimages = 1. The value is li</para>
  </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
